facts_and_links: {'Trivia': ['Paleontology aficionados have viewed the series as a spiritual successor to Walking with Dinosaurs (1999). Ironically, David Attenborough refused to do the narration on Walking with Dinosaurs (1999) because he was unwilling to support a fictitious wildlife documentary at the time. Attenborough has since changed his view leading to his work here.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt10324164/trivia/?ref_=tt_dyk_trv'], 'Goofs': ['Throughout the series, dromaeosaur dinosaurs (aka "raptors") are depicted with their long wing feathers lining the entire length of their arms, but most fossilized feather impressions show these feathers would have only extended to their elbows and not their upper arms.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt10324164/goofs/?tab=gf&ref_=tt_dyk_gf'], 'Connections': ["Referenced in AniMat's Crazy Cartoon Cast: The Nominees of the Big 50th (2023)", 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt10324164/movieconnections/?ref_=tt_dyk_cnn']}

facts_and_links: {'Trivia': ["The documentary includes a lot of David Bowie's unpublished personal material, including photos, home videos and some interviews on TV. Director Brett Morgen talked in person with Bowie's widow, top model Iman, for asking permission to use the material as tribute to Bowie. Although in a first moment she was reluctant to this idea, she was convinced by Morgen's previous works Cobain: Montage of Heck (2015) and Jane (2017) about singer Kurt Cobain and scientist Jane Goodall, where Morgen used personal material from each other to create artistic collages as tribute to them, instead to use in the way to make a classic biographic documentary.", 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9883832/trivia/?ref_=tt_dyk_trv'], 'Connections': ['Features Das Cabinet des Dr. Caligari (1920)', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9883832/movieconnections/?ref_=tt_dyk_cnn'], 'Soundtracks': ['Ian FishWritten by David BowiePerformed by David BowieCourtesy of RZO Music Inc.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9883832/soundtrack/?ref_=tt_dyk_snd']}
